FT  29 JUN 94 / Charity shop profits drop 10%
Profits at charity shops fell 10 per cent in the last year, a survey of
their finances said yesterday. The typical shop generated income each week
of Pounds 868 to produce a surplus over costs of Pounds 237 this year,
compared with income of Pounds 963 and a surplus of Pounds 262 last year,
the magazine NGO Finance said.
Nearly 90 per cent of income came from donated goods with the remainder from
bought-in goods and cash donations. The proportion of income from bought-in
goods fell 29 per cent over the last 12 months.
